{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Default value: 0. Value range: [0, 1]","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps","doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","title":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","modules":[{"name":"MapboxMaps"}],"externalID":"s:10MapboxMaps18FillExtrusionLayerV04fillD15CutoffFadeRangeAA5ValueOySdGSgvp","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","text":"Value"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double"},{"text":">?","kind":"text"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text",